One night in 1907, the group was playing cards at a casino in Juárez, Mexico when a fight broke out. Pershing was struck in the head with a bottle and sustained a concussion. He was rushed across the border to El Paso for treatment, where he remained unconscious for four days.

When he woke up, Pershing discovered that he had become something of a celebrity. His friends had spread word of his prowess at blackjack, and people were calling him "Black Jack." The nickname stuck, and Pershing went on to become one of America's most famous generals.

